From 0001000100010001000100010001000100010001 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Bootlin <feedback@bootlin.com>
Date: Sat, 1 Jun 2024 10:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] arm64: dts: ti: k3-am625-beagleplay: Add nunchuk on I2C3

Declare a Nintendo Wiimote extension (Nunchuk) device on the I2C3 bus,
which is exposed on the mikroBUS connector of the BeaglePlay board.
The Nunchuk uses I2C address 0x52.

Signed-off-by: Bootlin <feedback@bootlin.com>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/ti/k3-am625-beagleplay.dts | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/ti/k3-am625-beagleplay.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/ti/k3-am625-beagleplay.dts
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/ti/k3-am625-beagleplay.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/ti/k3-am625-beagleplay.dts
@@ -616,3 +616,10 @@
 &mcasp1 {
 	status = "disabled";
 };
+
+&main_i2c3 {
+	nunchuk: joystick@52 {
+		compatible = "nintendo,wiimote-extension";
+		reg = <0x52>;
+	};
+};
-- 
